# TrainerDex — The Ultimate Pokémon GO Companion

I genuinely think this has the potential to become one of the best Pokémon GO companion websites if executed well.

After reviewing your notes, this is clearly bigger than PokéGenie, LeekDuck, or PvPoke individually. Instead of solving only one problem, the goal is to build a **Trainer Operating System**: one place where trainers don't need to jump across 10 different websites.

That's a strong direction because today the Pokémon GO community constantly switches between:

- Official Pokémon GO website
- LeekDuck
- PvPoke
- Pokebattler
- GO Hub
- Reddit
- X (Twitter)
- YouTube
- Campfire

TrainerDex can unify all of these workflows.

---

## Master Project Prompt

### Project Overview

Design and develop a premium web application called **TrainerDex**.

TrainerDex should become the all-in-one platform every Pokémon GO trainer uses daily.

It should combine the following into one beautiful ecosystem:

- Pokédex
- Events
- Raid Guides
- PvP Team Builder
- Graphics
- News
- Tips
- Leaks
- Counters
- Research
- Collection Tracker
- Community

The product should feel like an **official Pokémon GO application**, not a typical website.

It should instantly communicate:

> "Everything you need for Pokémon GO is here."

